BT /F2 20.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 744.00 Tm (FollowThru Full Project Guide) Tj ET
BT /F2 14.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 703.00 Tm (1. What This Project Is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 670.00 Tm (FollowThru is a FastAPI backend that helps turn messy meeting inputs into structured) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 657.00 Tm (execution output.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 631.00 Tm (At a high level, it does four jobs:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 605.00 Tm (1. It accepts meeting content from APIs, Slack slash commands, Slack DMs, Slack app) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 592.00 Tm (mentions, and now Zoom recording links.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 579.00 Tm (2. It extracts structured intelligence such as summary, action items, decisions, risks,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 566.00 Tm (and open questions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 553.00 Tm (3. It turns that intelligence into Slack Canvas markdown.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 540.00 Tm (4. It stores workflow state in a relational database and optionally publishes the result) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 527.00 Tm (back to Slack.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 501.00 Tm (So the real product idea is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 475.00 Tm (- Input: notes, transcript, voice-command transcript, uploaded transcript file, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 462.00 Tm (recording link.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 449.00 Tm (- Processing: parse, summarize, extract execution intelligence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 436.00 Tm (- Output: a draft, a preview, chat guidance, or a published Slack Canvas.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 410.00 Tm (2. Architectural Style) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 377.00 Tm (The codebase is organized in layered form:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 351.00 Tm (- `app/api`: HTTP entry points.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 338.00 Tm (- `app/slack`: Slack-specific entry points and handlers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 325.00 Tm (- `app/domain`: business logic and schemas.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 312.00 Tm (- `app/integrations`: wrappers around external systems like Slack and OpenAI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 299.00 Tm (- `app/db`: persistence models, engine, sessions, and migrations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 286.00 Tm (- `app/workers`: background-processing components for Celery tasks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 260.00 Tm (This layout is useful because it separates:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 234.00 Tm (- transport logic from business logic,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 221.00 Tm (- pure workflow code from vendor APIs,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 208.00 Tm (- sync request handling from async background jobs,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 195.00 Tm (- data schemas from persistence schemas.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 169.00 Tm (3. Full Directory Structure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 136.00 Tm (### Root) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 110.00 Tm (- `.editorconfig`) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 97.00 Tm (Controls basic formatting consistency across editors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 60.00 84.00 Tm (- `.gitignore`) Tj ET
endstream
