BT /F2 14.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 497.00 Tm (4. Main Runtime Flows) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 464.00 Tm (### 4.1 API Chat Flow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 438.00 Tm (The route `POST /api/v1/followthru/chat` calls `handle_followthru_chat`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 412.00 Tm (That service:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 386.00 Tm (1. Normalizes and parses the request.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 373.00 Tm (2. Detects the mode: help, chat, preview, draft, or publish.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 360.00 Tm (3. Creates or loads a chat session.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 347.00 Tm (4. Stores the user message.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 334.00 Tm (5. Either:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 321.00 Tm (- generates a chat response, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 308.00 Tm (- runs extraction plus canvas workflow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 295.00 Tm (6. Stores the assistant reply.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 282.00 Tm (7. Returns a structured `FollowThruResponse`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 256.00 Tm (### 4.2 Voice Command Flow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 230.00 Tm (The route `POST /api/v1/followthru/voice-command` is similar to chat, but it treats the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 217.00 Tm (input as a speech-to-text transcript and can persist that source with `source_type=voice`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 191.00 Tm (### 4.3 Workflow Preview Flow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 165.00 Tm (The route `POST /api/v1/workflows/preview`:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 139.00 Tm (1. accepts raw meeting text,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 126.00 Tm (2. extracts structured intelligence,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 113.00 Tm (3. renders canvas markdown,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 100.00 Tm (4. returns the extraction plus draft markdown without storing a draft.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 74.00 Tm (This is useful for dry runs.) Tj ET
endstream
